Consider the Hilbert Space of weighted-square-integrable functions f(x): $$
\begin{equation}
\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}\frac{f(x)^2}{e^{x}+e^{-x}}dx<\infty.
\end{equation}
$$ Note this integral is taken over the real line in both directions, and the weighting is roughly exponential.  Hilbert Polynomials are complete using a different weighting, while Laguerre polynomials use a similar exponential weighting, but only on the positive real line. What is a simple proof or reference that polynomials are complete in this space?
